One part of Jeff Lemir's #MoonKnight run is that his DID is a consequence of once finding out that a Rabbi he liked from his childhood turned out to be a Nazi serial killer, and Marc discovered this by accidentally stumbling into this Nazi's torture dungeon. 1/

The way the issue revealed this was dark as fuck, that aspect of the story did not resolve in a happy way showing the Nazi get killed by Marc. He ran, the Nazi escaped, and Marc had that trauma with him as he grew. Mental health stories like this SHOULD be told on screen. 2/
@SPRNGCHARLIE both 😎

Of course, there are people who will find the things triggering, and that is unfortunate, and while the MCU is just, at its forefront, entertainment, the diversity of its characters present it with an opportunity to tell raw and real human stories. 3/

Sometimes minds are opened by the strangest of things, or in the most random of places. If watching Moon Knight creates greater understanding among the friends and relatives of people suffering with DID or Bipolar, or mental health in general, then it's an amazing achievement. 5/
